# Testing Environment Setup Guide

## 1. Browser Setup
```bash
# Create a clean browser profile for testing
Chrome: 
1. Open Chrome
2. Click Profile icon -> Add -> Create New Profile
3. Name it "Testing Profile"
4. Don't sync

Firefox:
1. Open Firefox
2. Menu -> New Private Window
```

## 2. Development Tools Setup
```bash
# Install React Developer Tools
1. Chrome Web Store -> React Developer Tools
2. Firefox Add-ons -> React Developer Tools

# Install Redux DevTools (if using Redux)
1. Chrome Web Store -> Redux DevTools
2. Firefox Add-ons -> Redux DevTools
```

## 3. Testing Database Setup
```bash
# Ensure test data doesn't interfere with production
1. Create test users:
   - test@example.com / Test123!
   - admin@example.com / Admin123!
   
2. Create test families:
   - Test Family 1 (2 members)
   - Test Family 2 (4 members)
```

## 4. Network Testing Tools
```bash
# Install Postman for API testing
1. Download Postman
2. Create a new collection "Family Hub Tests"
3. Set up environment variables:
   - baseUrl: http://localhost:xxxx
   - authToken: (to be filled after login)
```

## 5. Mobile Testing Setup
```bash
# Browser Developer Tools Mobile Emulation
1. Open DevTools (F12)
2. Toggle Device Toolbar (Ctrl+Shift+M)
3. Select different devices:
   - iPhone 12 Pro
   - iPad
   - Samsung Galaxy
```